Subject: [PATCH] feat: bridge Phase 1 implementation gaps

Wire ScanMode through analyzer, interpolate ${var} in remediation
templates, and add a minimal VS Code extension that runs the shared
analyzer-core on save.

- analyzer-core: filter rules by mode (fast=critical/high only, standard
  and deep run all rules; deep reserved for future external scanners)
- remediation-engine: new interpolate() helper expands ${name} in
  why/how/exampleFix using RuleMatch.variables; references untouched
- rules/injection: capture <table> in SQL concat and <target> in
  innerHTML so their exampleFix shows the actual identifier
- extensions/vscode: new workspace package providing on-save scanning
  (fast by default), VibeGuard: Scan File command, and Diagnostics

